, "text_bw": "zul~apN", "text_ar": "زُلَّةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a gift."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A feast,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "repast, that is prepared for guests."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, O, Msb.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ait~axa*a fulaAnN zal~apF", "text_ar": "اِتَّخَذَ فُلَانٌ زَلَّةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one made,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prepared, a feast for guests"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Lth, O, Msb.) Hence, (Lth, TA,) it is also a name for"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Food that is carried from the table of one's friend"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "relation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a word of the dial. of El-'Irák: (Lth, Msb, K:) or in this sense it is a vulgar word, (K, TA,) used by the common people of El-'Irák (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EurosN", "text_ar": "عُرْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A marriage-feast"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (ISh, Az, Msb, K.) So in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kun~aA fiY zal~api fulaAnK", "text_ar": "كُنَّا فِى زَلَّةِ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "We were at the marriage-feast of such a one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (ISh, Az, Msb, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "Lth", "TA", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}